net.commotionwireless.shell
Class Shell

java.lang.Object
  net.commotionwireless.shell.Shell
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable
public class Shell
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable

Shell is the singleton class that provides a Java interface to the fork shell. Processes running in a fork shell are represented as ShellProcesses. Process control (creation, start, stop) is done through ShellProcess-es. To start using a Shell, do the following: 

 Shell shell = Shell.getInstance();
 shell.setForkCmd("./fork"); //optional.
 shell.startShell();
